<subSubSection id="C3646FCDFFDEFF89FF73FCC146D9FC70" pageId="4" pageNumber="199" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC13C46FFDEFF89FF73FCC146D9FC70" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="B90AE054FFDEFF89FF73FCC14544FC9D" bold="true" box="[199,334,844,869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E47C5FFDEFF89FD10FCC146FAFC9C" authorityName="Hakimian &amp; Nozari &amp; Gharali &amp; Evenhuis" authorityYear="2018" box="[676,752,844,868]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Cyrtosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivitta">
<emphasis id="B90AE054FFDEFF89FD10FCC146FAFC9C" bold="true" box="[676,752,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">trivitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is composed of two Latin words: 
<emphasis id="B90AE054FFDEFF89FBC7FCC04087FC9C" box="[1139,1165,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">tri</emphasis>
[= three] + 
<emphasis id="B90AE054FFDEFF89FAA7FCC0414FFC9C" box="[1299,1349,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="199">vitta</emphasis>
[stripe] and refers to three black stripes on the mesonotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
